Biography
 Native of Muskegon, Michigan, U.S. Raised in an African-American enclave, was the second-oldest of nine children. His father was a foundry worker, and his mother was a housewife. Dean graduated from the Executive Management Program of Pennsylvania State University, continued to further his studies at Western Michigan University where he obtained a Bachelors Degree in Communications and a Masters Degree in Education. After a short period of working as a Teacher, in 1978, Dean went to work for Pharmacia and ...
