Interesting Facts
Having come from an underprivileged background, Dean was not very worldly, on the subject of seeing black olives for the first time in College, he recalled,: "There was a salad bar in the cafeteria. I reached in and took a handful because I figured they were grapes. Then I thought they were spoiled and that I was going to die. People started laughing at me."
Contact us to see more Interesting Facts
Interests, Passion, Hobbies

Kind of Interests, Passion and Hobbies: Music
Description: Appears to enjoy music. In an interview with the San Francisco Business Times, Dean admitted that the R&B genre was one of his three greatest passions.


Kind of Interests, Passion and Hobbies: Sports - Golf
Description: Appears to enjoy playing golf; Dean's golf handicap reportedly fluctuates between 15 and 18.


Kind of Interests, Passion and Hobbies: Business - Leadership
Description: Dean is a nationally recognized leader within and beyond the field of healthcare. As CEO and President of Dignity Health, Dean is responsible for the organization's $13 billion in assets, overall management, governance, strategy and direction.Through Dean's leadership which brought Dignity Health through significant strategic, operational, and financial transformations, the organization is now known as a leading healthcare organization that is recognized for high quality, compassionate care, operational excellence, and strong financial results.

Contact us to see more Interests, Passion, Hobbies
Philanthropy

Giving Profile: Dean is the President and CEO of Dignity Health, a not-for-profit healthcare company. He attended the 2013 Dignity Health Philanthropy Education Summit, which was held in Phoenix, Arizona, where he gets the yearly update of the charitable work done by Dignity Health. Dean is proactive in shaping the future of U.S. healthcare, and working toward public healthcare, trying to make it more available to citizens of lower income and the uninsured. He participates in reform discussions with President Barack Obama and staff at the White House and has been appointed to the State Health Care Cost Commission. Dean also took part in the Future of Healthcare Leadership Summit, where Bay Area business leaders discussed how President Obama's health reform law is being implemented in the state. In 2013 he was voted Humanitarian CEO of the Year.

